'''Hans E. B<U+00FC>hler''' (April 12, 1893 <U+2013> June 1, 1967) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[Equestrianism|horse rider]] who competed in the [[1924 Summer Olympics]].

In 1924 the and his horse ''Sailor Boy'' won the silver medal as part of the Swiss team in the team jumping competition, after finishing twentieth in the [[Equestrian at the 1924 Summer Olympics|individual jumping event]]. He and his horse ''Mikosch'' also participated in the [[Equestrian at the 1924 Summer Olympics|individual eventing]] and finished 14th. As member of the Swiss eventing team they finished fourth in the [[Equestrian at the 1924 Summer Olympics|team eventing]].

